<p>have a problem here with Symfony . I want to have virtual host on ubuntu so I can access my Symfony application like this app.local. What I have tried:</p>  <pre><code> &lt;VirtualHost *:80&gt;   ServerName app.local   &lt;IfModule mod_rewrite.c&gt;     RewriteEngine on     RewriteCond %{REQUEST_METHOD} ^(TRACE|TRACK)     RewriteRule .* - [F]   &lt;/IfModule&gt;   &lt;Directory /&gt;     Options FollowSymLinks     AllowOverride All   &lt;/Directory&gt;   DocumentRoot /var/www/app/web   &lt;Directory /var/www/app/web&gt;     Options Indexes FollowSymLinks MultiViews     AllowOverride All     Order allow,deny     allow from all     Require all granted   &lt;/Directory&gt; &lt;/VirtualHost&gt; </code></pre>  <p>I added these lines to hosts file</p>  <pre><code>127.0.0.1 app.local </code></pre>  <p>but when I write app.local in my browser, it brings the index of my www directory(default apache page). What am I doing wrong?</p>